reviews.review_text:
Get on the bus!! Don't miss this venues jams!! Vegas shows were incredible. The remoteness of  Vegas itself,  everyone travelled to get to the three shows which brought an even higher vibration of "journey" thus creating an epic emotional release beyond the normal highest standard we deadheads have been gifted with throughout this bands determined ascent of an everest-like  pursuit of creation. "searching for a new sound" phil  "furthur inquiry" Ken   YA Keep truckin' is one well used mantra for this crew and our hopes for the future expression of their music in performances from the remaining members and all artists. The WAY the shows are choreographed to the multiple show venue stops, the charities coupled with the GD song list would do the world a lot of good if it were continued intact once the original band members (gulp) retire. There is ALOT of GOOD THINGS happening here!!!! Thanks for the mental spa and all your efforts boys. 
Specifically in this 2nd show I  find myself returning  to the section where a hair-raising Terrapin jam moves into space and then spanish jam/space. It's a converter! ! To completely explain what this band does, and how, is impossible without being at a show physically, however, try bottling this masterpiece  with its spacial envelopment that follows!!!
Gratefully the soundboardmaestro
ps please send me a pointer of other incredible
shows/sections to enjoy! I'm looking for a new sound too!!! mmccauley33@yahoo.com

Ok recording  I was at this show. Though the lightning and thunder made the experience of this show unique, musically it is a 3 at best. Garcia is tentative and confused, presaging the doldrums of 1994/95, and widely stays low in the mix for much of this show. The previous day was little better, the day after even worse.
